@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place 'iTrix' where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed. However, your Workbench must have at least
4 colours.

                             How to play?

  Playing the game is a simple matter of clicking on any tile you
want to move. If it is next and connected by a coloured 'link' to
the empty space, that tile will move towards the empty space.

  When two tiles of the same type are placed next, and are linked
to each other; these tiles will 'explode' and disappear, leaving
empty tiles. The link that connected those tiles will also
disappear... so watch out that other tiles are not isolated in
impossible to reach locations afterwards...

  A game board can be restarted at any time by clicking on the
'Restart' button. However, the number of moves you make on each
game board will accumulate until you complete that board.

  You can change the colour of the links by clicking on the
'Colours' button, this will cycle through the available colours
(up to 16 colours) from the Workbench palette.

  Have fun!

@endnode

